5|$|Like {{other public}} {{universities}} in Brazil, Unicamp {{is almost entirely}} funded by the government, {{in this particular case}} of the State of São Paulo. Funding is provided mainly from <b>sales</b> <b>taxes,</b> but a small percentage of total budget is obtained from donations, paid extension programs and corporate sponsors.|$|E
5|$|The Youngstown area {{is served}} by the Western Reserve Transit Authority (WRTA) bus system, which is {{supported}} through Mahoning County property and <b>sales</b> <b>taxes.</b> WRTA, whose main terminal is in the downtown area, provides service throughout the city and into surrounding Mahoning and Trumbull counties. The downtown terminal serves as the Youngstown area's Greyhound terminal.|$|E
