25|$|The state <b>sales</b> <b>tax</b> in Kansas is 6.15%. Various {{cities and}} {{counties}} in Kansas have an additional local <b>sales</b> <b>tax.</b> Except during the 2001 recession (March–November 2001) when monthly <b>sales</b> <b>tax</b> collections were flat, collections have trended higher as the economy has grown and two rate increases have been enacted. If {{there had been no}} change in <b>sales</b> <b>tax</b> rates, and no change in the economy, the total <b>sales</b> <b>tax</b> collections for 2003 should have been $1,797million, compared to $805.3million in 1990, but instead they amounted to $1,630million an inflation adjusted reduction of 10%.|$|R
